<p>Data type for signed integer values, strictly 64 bits (8 bytes)
long.</p>

<p>Per definition, this data type would use 63 bits for value, 1 bit for
sign, thus allowing representation of integer numbers in the following
range:</p>

<ul>
<li>Minimum: -9&thinsp;223&thinsp;372&thinsp;036&thinsp;854&thinsp;775&thinsp;808</li>
<li>Maximum: 9&thinsp;223&thinsp;372&thinsp;036&thinsp;854&thinsp;775&thinsp;807</li>
</ul>
